{"id":"019de369-c341-73c2-9bca-ed0d91c7e474","archived":1,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail","title":"Handrail QA Daily Simulator Sweep","first_user_message":"Automation: Handrail QA Daily Simulator Sweep\nAutomation ID: handrail-simulator-bug-sweep\nAutomation memory: $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-simulator-bug-sweep/memory.md\nLast run: 2026-04-30T17:00:39.499Z (1777568439499)\n\nAct as the Handrail QA daily simulator sweep sidecar. Work in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail on the current local branch. Inspect docs/team/qa-lead.md and docs/team/README.md first. Run the documented full iPhone and iPad simulator confidence sweep for Handrail. Walk the documented UI paths in UI_PATHS.md, use UI_PATH_ISSUES.md and docs/production_readiness_report.md as known-risk context, and re-verify any issues marked done or claimed fixed since the last run. Save commands, device targets, screenshots, and notes under test-artifacts/. Create or update GitHub issues in zfifteen/handrail only for reproducible findings, label new issues as bug plus the affected platform label, and include reproduction steps, expected behavior, observed behavior, and evidence paths. For all GitHub reads and writes, use the local `gh` CLI only; do not use GitHub app, connector, or MCP tools, because connector permission prompts block unattended automation. If `gh auth status` is not already authenticated for zfifteen/handrail, record that as a blocker instead of requesting interactive permission. Preserve unrelated local changes and never revert work you did not make. Leave a concise final summary naming evidence paths, issues touched, remaining blockers, and verification performed.","rollout_path":"/Users/velocityworks/.codex/archived_sessions/rollout-2026-05-01T08-00-52-019de369-c341-73c2-9bca-ed0d91c7e474.jsonl","created_at":"2026-05-01 12:00:52","updated_at":"2026-05-01 12:31:17"},
