{"id":"019de28f-5429-7b51-87c2-cf77021ba1d4","archived":0,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/Documents/Codex/2026-05-01/context-for-new-codex-session-repo","title":"Update xAI chaining support","first_user_message":"Context for new Codex session:\n\nRepo: /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail\n\nRecent task:\nWe updated the local xAI second-opinion harness to support stateful conversations through xAI response chaining.\n\nImportant paths:\n- /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/xai_harness\n- /Users/velocityworks/.codex/skills/second-opinion/SKILL.md\n- /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail\n\nxAI harness changes made in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/xai_harness:\n- Added `previous_response_id` to `SecondOpinionRequest`.\n- Added `response_id` to `SecondOpinionResponse`.\n- Updated `xai_second_opinion(...)` MCP entrypoint to accept `previous_response_id`.\n- Changed the xAI client call path from `store_messages=False` to `store_messages=True`.\n- On first turn, it sends the system instruction normally.\n- On follow-up turns, it passes `previous_response_id` and does not replay the system/history.\n- It now validates that xAI returned a non-empty response id.\n- Updated tests for request defaults, empty previous_response_id rejection, MCP entrypoint argument passing, request builder chaining, response_id parsing, and usage handling.\n- `python3 -m pytest` in `/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/xai_harness` passed: 22/22.\n- `git diff --check` passed.\n\nSkill instruction update:\n- `/Users/velocityworks/.codex/skills/second-opinion/SKILL.md` now says follow-up calls should pass the prior tool result’s `response_id` as `previous_response_id` instead of replaying the transcript.\n\nValidation already performed:\n- Existing native MCP tool schema in the old Codex session was stale and did not expose `previous_response_id`.\n- The bundled stdio MCP path did expose the updated harness behavior.\n- Three-round state test through stdio MCP passed:\n  - Round 1 returned `response_id: 96b1d5e8-2f37-f31d-870a-e77c1324755c`\n  - Round 2 passed that as `previous_response_id` and Grok recalled marker `BLUE-RAIL-731`\n  - Round 2 returned `response_id: 920fe618-956c-95fb-b6ab-9f907550f3f1`\n  - Round 3 passed that id and Grok again recalled `BLUE-RAIL-731`, concluding validation pass.\n- Stale `xai-harness` processes were killed.\n- Python introspection after killing stale processes showed:\n  `xai_second_opinion(problem, context='', desired_output=..., allow_search=False, max_output_tokens=2048, previous_response_id=None) -> dict`\n- Model schema introspection showed request includes `previous_response_id` and response includes `response_id`.\n\nNeed to verify in the new session:\n1. Use tool discovery for `xai_second_opinion`.\n2. Confirm the native MCP schema now exposes `previous_response_id`.\n3. Run a short two- or three-round native MCP state test:\n   - Round 1: ask Grok to remember a marker.\n   - Capture returned `response_id`.\n   - Round 2: pass only `previous_response_id`, do not restate marker.\n   - Confirm Grok recalls marker.\n4. If native schema still does not expose `previous_response_id`, use the stdio fallback script:\n   `/Users/velocityworks/.codex/skills/second-opinion/scripts/call_second_opinion.py`\n\nRelated Handrail repo work:\n- Root `.gitignore` now ignores `AGENTS.md`.\n- Local-only `/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail/AGENTS.md` was created with Handrail local-first agent instructions and is ignored.\n- Added tracked `/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail/docs/product-invariants.md`.\n- Updated Handrail role docs under `/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail/docs/team/` to require `Product Invariant Check`.\n- Generated transcript:\n  `/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail/docs/transcripts/grok-handrail-30-rounds-2026-05-01.md`","rollout_path":"/Users/velocityworks/.codex/sessions/2026/05/01/rollout-2026-05-01T04-02-17-019de28f-5429-7b51-87c2-cf77021ba1d4.jsonl","created_at":"2026-05-01 08:02:17","updated_at":"2026-05-01 08:03:24"},
{"id":"019de1c8-5cd5-7d92-8655-a690af493c72","archived":0,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail","title":"Handrail PM","first_user_message":"Automation: Handrail PM\nAutomation ID: handrail-pm\nAutomation memory: $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-pm/memory.md\nLast run: 2026-05-01T01:23:41.507Z (1777598621507)\n\nAct as the Handrail PM defined in docs/team/pm.md. Work in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail on the current local branch. Preserve unrelated user changes and never revert work you did not make. Use zfifteen/handrail as the GitHub repository target when creating or updating issues, milestones, or releases. For all GitHub reads and writes, use the local `gh` CLI only; do not use GitHub app, connector, or MCP tools, because connector permission prompts block unattended automation. If `gh auth status` is not already authenticated for zfifteen/handrail, record that as a blocker instead of requesting interactive permission. Inspect docs/team/pm.md and docs/team/README.md first. At the start of the run, check recent Slack messages in #handrail-agents (channel C0B0K6B0T6K) addressed to Handrail PM, plus any handoff note at $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-pm/handoff.md when present. Treat Slack as an operational inbox; write durable state to repo docs, GitHub issues, or handoff files before posting Slack requests to another role. A Slack request is handled only when the receiving role records the Slack Subject and message timestamp in its report or durable handoff response. Review the relevant roadmap, readiness, issue, milestone, release, and repo state. This automation runs every six hours; use each run as an extensive PM work block, not a light status check. Complete multiple concrete PM actions when they are independent, deterministic, and within PM ownership. You may edit code, tests, docs, and GitHub issues/milestones/releases when that is the smallest concrete human-equivalent action for the PM role. Prefer one narrow deterministic path per artifact or decision. Leave clear evidence of actions taken, files or issues touched, remaining blockers, and verification performed. If writing a report, write the latest PM report to docs/team/outputs/pm.md. Do not run another Handrail team role, manually launch another role, call app-server thread creation, edit automation records, or edit automation database rows as a handoff mechanism. Then stop.","rollout_path":"/Users/velocityworks/.codex/sessions/2026/05/01/rollout-2026-05-01T00-24-57-019de1c8-5cd5-7d92-8655-a690af493c72.jsonl","created_at":"2026-05-01 04:24:57","updated_at":"2026-05-01 07:56:22"},
{"id":"019de25b-4fe7-7c41-bd51-1d3d2c32d438","archived":0,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail","title":"Handrail Lead Dev","first_user_message":"Automation: Handrail Lead Dev\nAutomation ID: handrail-lead-dev\nAutomation memory: $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-lead-dev/memory.md\nLast run: 2026-05-01T06:04:58.005Z (1777615498005)\n\nAct as the Handrail lead dev defined in docs/team/lead-dev.md. Work in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail on the current local branch. Preserve unrelated user changes and never revert work you did not make. Use zfifteen/handrail as the GitHub repository target when creating or updating issues. For all GitHub reads and writes, use the local `gh` CLI only; do not use GitHub app, connector, or MCP tools, because connector permission prompts block unattended automation. If `gh auth status` is not already authenticated for zfifteen/handrail, record that as a blocker instead of requesting interactive permission. Inspect docs/team/lead-dev.md and docs/team/README.md first. Treat the Codex automation home as /Users/velocityworks/.codex even when CODEX_HOME is unset; do not create or write /automations. At the start of the run, check recent Slack messages in #handrail-agents (channel C0B0K6B0T6K) addressed to Handrail Lead Dev, plus any lead-dev handoff note at /Users/velocityworks/.codex/automations/handrail-lead-dev/handoff.md when present and readable. Treat Slack as an operational inbox; write durable state to repo docs, GitHub issues, or writable handoff files before posting Slack requests to another role. A Slack request is handled only when the receiving role records the Slack Subject and message timestamp in its report or durable handoff response. Choose exactly one implementation target using this priority order: addressed Slack request with durable artifact or issue, /Users/velocityworks/.codex/automations/handrail-lead-dev/handoff.md when present and readable, concrete open GitHub bug issue with reproduction or acceptance criteria, concrete open GitHub enhancement issue, then one hygiene patch with an obvious verification path. If a readable handoff exists, complete or explicitly block that handoff before selecting unrelated GitHub work. This automation runs every hour; each run must complete or explicitly block one complete feature, bug, or hygiene target end-to-end. Review current git status, roadmap/readiness findings, active issues, source files, and nearby tests. You may edit code, tests, docs, and GitHub issues when that is the smallest concrete human-equivalent action for the lead dev role. Prefer one narrow deterministic path. Leave clear evidence of actions taken, files or issues touched, remaining blockers, and verification performed. If writing a report, write the latest lead dev report to docs/team/outputs/lead-dev.md. For iPhone or iPad simulator validation, use XcodeBuildMCP rather than a duplicate direct shell `xcodebuild ... -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,...'` command when XcodeBuildMCP can provide the same build, test, launch, or screenshot evidence. After implementation work, write or refresh a QA handoff note at /Users/velocityworks/.codex/automations/handrail-qa-lead/handoff.md when validation is needed only if that file path is writable. If the QA handoff path is not writable, do not attempt the write; record the intended QA handoff content and the writability blocker in docs/team/outputs/lead-dev.md instead. QA Lead runs independently on its own schedule. Do not run another Handrail team role, manually launch another role, call app-server thread creation, edit automation records, edit automation database rows, or retry blocked filesystem operations as a handoff mechanism. Then stop.","rollout_path":"/Users/velocityworks/.codex/sessions/2026/05/01/rollout-2026-05-01T03-05-28-019de25b-4fe7-7c41-bd51-1d3d2c32d438.jsonl","created_at":"2026-05-01 07:05:28","updated_at":"2026-05-01 07:36:56"},
