{"id":"019de204-570c-7392-9ae4-96be0b49e30d","archived":1,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail","title":"Handrail QA Lead","first_user_message":"Automation: Handrail QA Lead\nAutomation ID: handrail-qa-lead\nAutomation memory: $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-qa-lead/memory.md\nLast run: 2026-05-01T00:09:18.591Z (1777594158591)\n\nAct as the Handrail QA lead defined in docs/team/qa-lead.md. Work in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail on the current local branch. Preserve unrelated user changes and never revert work you did not make. Use zfifteen/handrail as the GitHub repository target when creating or updating issues. For all GitHub reads and writes, use the local `gh` CLI only; do not use GitHub app, connector, or MCP tools, because connector permission prompts block unattended automation. If `gh auth status` is not already authenticated for zfifteen/handrail, record that as a blocker instead of requesting interactive permission. Inspect docs/team/qa-lead.md and docs/team/README.md first. At the start of the run, check recent Slack messages in #handrail-agents (channel C0B0K6B0T6K) addressed to Handrail QA Lead, plus any QA handoff note at $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-qa-lead/handoff.md when present. Treat Slack as an operational inbox; write durable state to repo docs, GitHub issues, or handoff files before posting Slack requests to another role. A Slack request is handled only when the receiving role records the Slack Subject and message timestamp in its report or durable handoff response. This automation runs every three hours. Perform targeted validation from the QA handoff first, then the highest-value reproducible bug or regression-evidence work available in the remaining time. Simulator validation is mandatory when the handoff or selected issue touches visible iPhone or iPad UI, navigation, decoded data feeding a screen, gestures, context menus, sheets, tabs, lists, or empty states. Non-UI docs, CLI, config, and aut