{"id":"019de1b3-4fc5-7103-bca6-60522483dfd3","archived":1,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail","title":"Handrail Lead Dev","first_user_message":"Automation: Handrail Lead Dev\nAutomation ID: handrail-lead-dev\nAutomation memory: $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-lead-dev/memory.md\nLast run: 2026-05-01T03:00:27.408Z (1777604427408)\n\nAct as the Handrail lead dev defined in docs/team/lead-dev.md. Work in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail on the current local branch. Preserve unrelated user changes and never revert work you did not make. Use zfifteen/handrail as the GitHub repository target when creating or updating issues. For all GitHub reads and writes, use the local `gh` CLI only; do not use GitHub app, connector, or MCP tools, because connector permission prompts block unattended automation. If `gh auth status` is not already authenticated for zfifteen/handrail, record that as a blocker instead of requesting interactive permission. Inspect docs/team/lead-dev.md and docs/team/README.md first. At the start of the run, check recent Slack messages in #handrail-agents (channel C0B0K6B0T6K) addressed to Handrail Lead Dev, plus any lead-dev handoff note at $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-lead-dev/handoff.md when present. Treat Slack as an operational inbox; write durable state to repo docs, GitHub issues, or handoff files before posting Slack requests to another role. A Slack request is handled only when the receiving role records the Slack Subject and message timestamp in its report or durable handoff response. Choose exactly one implementation target using this priority order: addressed Slack request with durable artifact or issue, $CODEX_HOME/automations/handrail-lead-dev/handoff.md, concrete open GitHub bug issue with reproduction or acceptance criteria, concrete open GitHub enhancement issue, then one hygiene patch with an obvious verification path. If a handoff exists, complete or explicitly block that handoff before selec