{"id":"019ddf4e-ffc6-7e82-902d-d568a7b14440","archived":1,"source":"vscode","cwd":"/Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail","title":"Finish Handrail iPad App","first_user_message":"Automation: Finish Handrail iPad App\nAutomation ID: finish-handrail-ipad-app\nAutomation memory: $CODEX_HOME/automations/finish-handrail-ipad-app/memory.md\nLast run: 2026-04-30T15:51:09.275Z (1777564269275)\n\nContinue the GitHub issue #6 iPad Handrail implementation using the incremental-coder process from /Users/velocityworks/.codex/skills/incremental-coder/SKILL.md. Work in /Users/velocityworks/IdeaProjects/handrail. Start from the current repository state and the revised issue plan at https://github.com/zfifteen/handrail/issues/6. Produce exactly one complete bounded iteration per run: inspect status, identify the next unfinished implementation or final-acceptance item, implement only that item, run the repo-native validation required by the plan, and commit the completed iteration with an appropriate conventional commit message. If all implementation and acceptance items are complete, do not make code changes; report that the iPad app is complete and leave the repo untouched. Preserve unrelated dirty work: do not stage, revert, or edit existing unrelated CLI changes or untracked issue-artifact files unless the selected iteration explicitly requires them. Use deterministic straight-line changes only, LF line endings, and no fallback paths or broad refactors. Standard validation commands are: `cd cli && npm test`, `xcodebuild -project ios/Handrail/Handrail.xcodeproj -scheme Handrail -destination 'generic/platform=iOS Simulator' build`, `xcodebuild test -project ios/Handrail/Handrail.xcodeproj -scheme Handrail -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPad Pro 13-inch (M5)'`, and for root/transcript/command/window or final acceptance work also `xcodebuild -project ios/Handrail/Handrail.xcodeproj -scheme Handrail -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17' build`. At the end of each run, summarize the iteration completed, commit hash if any, validation results, and the next remaining item.","rollout_path":"/Users/velocityworks/.codex/archived_sessions/rollout-2026-04-30T12-53-09-019ddf4e-ffc6-7e82-902d-d568a7b14440.jsonl","created_at":"2026-04-30 16:53:09","updated_at":"2026-04-30 17:23:52"},
